label: TYPE
description: This field identifies the purpose of the Hold record.

label: ACHRECURRINGSTOP
description: This field indicates whether the Hold record is used to stop multiple ACH items.

label: EFFECTIVEDATE
description: this field stores the date the hold should take effect or the date the hold was created for hold types 1–12 and 14–21, and for hold type (13) Loan Draft, it stores the date a preapproved loan draft form was issued to the member.

label: EXPIRATIONDATE
description: This field stores the expiration date of the hold.

label: EXPIRATIONTIME
description: This field stores the time when a hold should be released.

label: RECORDCHANGEDATE
description: This field stores the system date when you create, change or save the Hold record.

label: HOLDCREATIONDATE
description: This field stores the AIX date (mm/dd/yyyy) that you created the hold record.

label: HOLDCREATIONTIME
description: This field stores the AIX time (hh:mm:ss) that you created the hold record.

label: MATCHDATE
description: This field stores the date of an authorization hold.

label: MATCHTIME
description: This field stores the time of an authorization hold.

label: TRANSACTIONTYPE
description: This field identifies the transaction type for ATM and PIN authorization transactions for preauthorized Loan holds only.

label: FEECODE
description: This field stores the code that determines the fee placed on the transaction.

label: AMOUNT
description: This field stores the amount of money held.

label: LEDGERBALANCE
description: This field stores the balance that the ATM software uses when it creates a PIN authorization or signature authorization Hold record.

label: AVAILABLEBALANCE
description: This field stores the value calculated by an ATM to authorize a transaction.

label: REFERENCE1
description: All the Reference # fields, store reference information that is related to the hold.

label: REFERENCE2
description: All the Reference # fields, store reference information that is related to the hold.

label: PAYEENAME
description: The value in this field varies depending on the hold type.

label: MEMBERBRANCH
description: This field is used by corporate credit unions only and it stores the branch number if available.

label: STOPPAYCODE
description: This field stores the reason given for a stop.

label: REFERENCE3
description: All the Reference # fields, store reference information that is related to the hold.

label: REFERENCE4
description: All the Reference # fields, store reference information that is related to the hold.

label: LOCATOR
description: This field value in each record is unique for each member account.

label: FEEDESCRIPTION
description: This field stores the description in the Fee Code field.
